        <details><summary>What's the dress code?</summary><div>Dress to impress — the clubs require it. No flip-flops, sports jerseys, workout clothes, baseball caps, or offensive graphics. Smart casual or club attire. No dress code to board the bus itself.</div></details>
        <details><summary>Is our group 100% private?</summary><div>Absolutely. Your group is never paired with strangers and we never sell individual tickets. Private bus, private lounge, private nightclub entry — the entire experience is exclusively yours from start to finish.</div></details>
        <details><summary>Can we bring our own drinks?</summary><div>Yes — BYOB is fully welcome on the bus. We also include complimentary champagne, mixers, ice, cups, straws, and napkins. Drink responsibly — all guests must be 21+.</div></details>
        <details><summary>What if someone in our group is under 21?</summary><div>All guests must be 21+ with valid ID, verified at multiple checkpoints. The only exception: 21st birthday guests are welcome if the reservation begins at midnight or later.</div></details>
      </div>
      <div class="faq">
        <details><summary>How far in advance should we book?</summary><div>1–2 weeks for regular weekends. For major events (EDC, Memorial Day, 4th of July, NYE, SEMA, G2E) book 4–6 weeks ahead — those fill extremely fast.</div></details>
